From: Nicolas Michaut <nicolas@yumilab.com>
Subject: [PATCH] board: sunxi: add SmartPi One defconfig
Date: 2026-04-24

Add defconfig for the Yumi Lab SmartPi One board.
Based on nanopi_m1_defconfig (same Allwinner H3 SoC).

DRAM tuned to 576 MHz with ZQ calibration and ODT enabled
for improved memory stability.

Signed-off-by: Nicolas Michaut <nicolas@yumilab.com>
---
 configs/smartpi1_defconfig | 12 ++++++++++++
 1 file changed, 12 insertions(+)
 create mode 100644 configs/smartpi1_defconfig

diff --git a/configs/smartpi1_defconfig b/configs/smartpi1_defconfig
new file mode 100644
--- /dev/null
+++ b/configs/smartpi1_defconfig
@@ -0,0 +1,12 @@
+CONFIG_ARM=y
+CONFIG_ARCH_SUNXI=y
+CONFIG_DEFAULT_DEVICE_TREE="sun8i-h3-nanopi-m1"
+CONFIG_DRAM_CLK=576
+CONFIG_DRAM_ZQ=3881979
+CONFIG_DRAM_ODT_EN=y
+CONFIG_SPL=y
+CONFIG_MACH_SUN8I_H3=y
+# CONFIG_SYS_MALLOC_CLEAR_ON_INIT is not set
+CONFIG_USB_EHCI_HCD=y
+CONFIG_USB_OHCI_HCD=y
+CONFIG_SYS_BOARD="smartpi1"
--
2.43.0
